A parental control shall allow the subscriber, in a commercially reasonable manner, to:
Block all access to the Internet; and
Block a child's access to websites by specifying prohibited websites or by selecting a category of sites to block;
Restrict a child's access exclusively to websites that the subscriber approves or a category of websites that the subscriber approves;
Restrict a child's access to websites that the parental control provider designates; or
Monitor a child's use of the Internet by providing a report to the subscriber indicating:
